      <link>/wiaposts/the-meaning-of-nishkam-karma/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 13 Jul 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/the-meaning-of-nishkam-karma/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5195-The-Meaning-Of-Nishkam-Karma.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;The Meaning of Nishkam Karma&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The Meaning of Nishkam Karma 
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-meaning-of-nishkam-karma&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#the-meaning-of-nishkam-karma&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Sanskrit language, the word Kriya means that which happens. Karma means which is done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whatever needs to be done for that you need to have your desire and intention. In Sanskrit it is called Sankalp. So without Sankalp, you cannot do any karma.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
